**C1.** W2 evidence doc (`docs/evidence/w2-timeout-staging-proof-2026-07-09.md`) says commit 67fff296 *"removes the override in nix/node-b.nix and start-services.sh."* Imprecise â€” it *changed* the override 180sâ†’60s (`nix/node-b.nix:350` `"PROXY_VMCTL_TIMEOUT=60s"`; `start-services.sh:126` `${PROXY_VMCTL_TIMEOUT:-60s}`). Functional claim (60s bound) is verified by the staging log `timeout=1m0s` and `max_duration_ms: 60001`. Wording nit only; deliverable bar met.

**C2.** The D-PROMO test legitimately uses `DOLT_RESET --hard` for rollback mechanics (`dolt_branch_isolation_pinned_test.go:28-29`, test-only). gpt55 previously cautioned against normalizing it as production rollback; I4 + the spec scope header already forbid it in production. No action â€” correctly scoped as test-only.

